\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces Corner-view 3D schematic of the loss landscape. The anchor and retained candidate checkpoints lie inside one connected valley. A uniform interval soup can drift toward a worse point if it averages too broadly, whereas D-COLA biases the soup toward a lower-loss location by combining worst-domain selection with locality-aware weighting. This is an illustrative geometry figure, not an empirical measurement.}}{9}{figure.6}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:landscape3d}{{6}{9}{Corner-view 3D schematic of the loss landscape. The anchor and retained candidate checkpoints lie inside one connected valley. A uniform interval soup can drift toward a worse point if it averages too broadly, whereas D-COLA biases the soup toward a lower-loss location by combining worst-domain selection with locality-aware weighting. This is an illustrative geometry figure, not an empirical measurement}{figure.6}{}}
