\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces Why D-COLA adds locality and covariance to worst-domain fit. Left: averaging across a barrier can leave the low-loss basin. Right: the target-risk certificate is modeled as worst-domain fit plus redundancy and locality penalties, up to constants not controllable without target labels.}}{10}{figure.7}\protected@file@percent }
